  <div class="banner">
    <h1>Bheem Singh</h1>
    <p>Doctoral Candidate in Hypersonic Flow Physics & Plasma Simulation</p>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="section">
      <h2>About</h2>
      <p>Bheem Singh is a doctoral student in Aerospace Engineering specializing in hypersonic aerothermodynamics, non-equilibrium plasma flows, and advanced numerical methods. With a strong foundation in CFD and high-temperature gas dynamics, he contributes to multi-physics modeling and simulation of re-entry phenomena, high-speed propulsion systems, and data-driven flow decomposition.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>M.Tech (Aerospace Engineering)</strong> – DIAT, Pune (2022–2024)</li>
        <li><strong>B.Tech (Aeronautical Engineering)</strong> – AKTU, Uttar Pradesh (2015–2019)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Research Interests</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Hypersonic Flow Simulation & Re-entry Aerothermodynamics</li>
        <li>Plasma Flow and Maxwell-Poisson Coupled Solvers</li>
        <li>Two-Temperature Models & Chemical Non-Equilibrium</li>
        <li>Reduced Order Modeling (POD, DMD, DMDSP)</li>
        <li>Multiphysics Coupled Solvers in High-Speed Environments</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Projects</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Grid Fin Optimization (DRDO Project)</strong> – Aerodynamic and thermal analysis of grid/cascade fins using ANSYS/Star CCM+ for advanced missiles.</li>
        <li><strong>Hypersonic Nose Cone Flow Analysis</strong> – CFD simulation of various nose cone shapes to improve drag and thermal efficiency.</li>
        <li><strong>Ramjet Engine Simulation</strong> – Internal flow analysis for ramjet configurations under supersonic regimes.</li>
        <li><strong>Toroidal vs Conventional Propeller Analysis</strong> – Evaluated flow dynamics and performance gains using CFD tools.</li>
        <li><strong>DMDSP on Hypersonic Jet LES Data</strong> – Applied sparse dynamic mode decomposition to identify coherent structures in high-speed jets.</li>
        <li><strong>Plasma Electromagnetic Solver</strong> – Coupled Maxwell-Poisson solver integrated with reacting gas models for plasma-aided flow control.</li>
        <li><strong>Full Hypersonic Solver Framework</strong> – Modular codebase including chemical non-equilibrium, species transport, and GUI-driven post-processing.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Publications</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>“CFD Simulation of High AoA with Gap Variation in Cascade Fins”, ICAME 2023</li>
        <li>“Numerical Study of Cascade Fins in Subsonic Regime at Multiple Mach”, STAAR 2024</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

